 -- MOO v1.9.0 (Hell variant): new wizard help topics --
2
 
2
 See "help <topic>" for more information:
2

2
Overview topics: 
2
  memtrace       -- new C functionality, for alloc/free logging.
2
  
2
Functions:
2
  set_live_trace() -- turn on memory tracing (when compiled in)
2

2
(Also see 'help changes'.)
29
5
4
21
2
memtrace: memory tracing inside the server
2

2
Every complex type (STR, LIST, HASH, FLOAT) is allocated and freed using functions that track
2
the number of references there are to variables, so that the variables can be freed when there 
2
are no longer any references to them.
2

2
When MEMORY_TRACE is defined in storage.h, all of this reference-juggling is dumped to the 
2
server logs. It can get very large in a hurry. To pare it down, MEMORY_TRACE_TYPE, when 
2
defined as a valid memory type, limits logging to only actions involving that memory type.
2

2
Further, memory tracing is not actually done until a call of set_live_trace(1). From 
2
that point on, all newly allocated memory (subject to type restrictions if active) is 
2
tracked and everything that happens to those blocks of memory will be dumped to the logs.
2

2
When set_live_trace(0) is called, no more new allocations will be logged, but events 
2
involving previously traced blocks of memory will continue to be logged.
2

2
Finally, at server shutdown, all traced memory blocks which still are resident in memory
2
will have their details (including type, memory location, reference count, and a C 
2
backtrace of the last event involving that memory) printed to the server log, in a section
2
delineated by the string "--- MEMCHECK ---" (for easy log-searching.)
29
5
4
20
2
Syntax:   set_live_trace   ( INT live_trace_on (1 or 0) ) => 0
2

2
  If memory tracing has been compiled into the server, (see 
2
  'help memtrace'), this will set the live trace flag to 
2
  the given value.
2
  
2
  When live tracing is active, every single allocation, 
2
  reference count check, and memory free will be written 
2
  to the server log. The type of memory this will track
2
  can be restricted by the MEMORY_TRACE_TYPE 
2
  preprocessor definition. Read 'help memtrace' for more 
2
  details on how this all works, and the source code.
2
  
2
  Long story short, you will never use this in any 
2
  kind of production environment.
2
  
2
Errors:
2
  E_TYPE:   if a_hash isn't a hash.
2
  E_PERM:   if player or programmer isn't a wizard.
2

