Syntax:  memory_usage ()   => list
2

2
On HellMOO, this is a list of numbers indicating the number of 
2
allocations currently in use, for each type of memory as defined
2
in the server code.
2

2
     {<total-allocations>, <type-1-allocs>, <type-2-allocs>, ...}
2

2
To see a list of all the memory types and what they (might) mean,
2
see 'help memory-types'.
2

2
On servers for which such statistics are not available, `memory_usage()'
2
returns `{}'.  The compilation option `USE_SYSTEM_MALLOC' controls
2
whether or not statistics are available; if the option is provided, statistics
2
are not available.
