*** NOTE: for more help on any verb, do 'help $mu:verbname'.
2

2
$match_utils ($mu) helps select objects from lists, by matching strings.
2

2
  Usually what you want:
2
:match          (str, obj-list)   => object in list matching str
2
:match_many     (str, obj-list)   => all objs in list matching str
2
:match_bodyref  (str, creature-list) => {creature, bodypart-obj}
2

2
  Usually not what you want:
2
:match_nth      (str, obj-list, n)=> nth object in list matching str
2
:match_verb     (verbname, obj)   => use prepstr etc to find verb on obj
2
:parse_ordinal_reference   ("fifth gun") => {5, "gun"}
2
:parse_possessive_reference("bob's gun") => {"bob", "gun"}
2
:object_match_failed (failedmatch, string [,ambigs])
2
    => Tell player why their object match failed.
