*** NOTE: for more help on any verb, do 'help $lu:verbname'.
2

2
$list_utils ($lu) provide verbs for working with lists, creating lists, 
2
and working with lists-of-lists (association lists or alists.) Verbs marked 
2
with asterisks (*) have suspending versions, named "(verbname)_suspended".
2

2
  Standard operations:
2
:append            (list,list,..) => result of concatenating the given lists
2
:reverse *         (list)         => reversed list
2
:remove_duplicates (list)         => list with all duplicates removed
2
:compress          (list)         => list with consecutive duplicates removed
2
:setremove_all     (list,elt)     => list with all occurrences of elt removed
2
:find_insert       (sortedlist,e) => index of first element >e in sortedlist
2
:sort *            (list[,keys])  => list, sorted in ascending order
2
:count             (elt,list)     => count of elt found in list
2
:flatten           (list)         => turn list of lists into one list
2
:randomly_permute *(list)         => shuffled list
2
:longest           (list)         => longest in list (strings or lists)
2
:shortest          (list)         => shortest in list (strings or lists)
2
:random            (list)         => use list[random($)] instead
2
:count_list *      (list)         => { {item1, count1}, {item2, count2}...}
2
:list_is_a         (list, obj)    => elts from list that descend from obj
2
:is_one_of         (obj, list)    => elts of list that are parents of obj
2

2
:remove_if(_not) * (o, v, list, @args)
2
    => list with elements removed which return true (false) for o:v(elt, @args)
2

2
:make              (n[,e])        => list of n copies of e
2
:range             (m,n)          => {m,m+1,...,n}
2
:as_list           (v)            => typeof(v) == LIST ? v | {v}
2
:break_at          (list, n)      => break list into chunks of max size n
2

2
:arrayset          (list,val,i[,j,k...])
2
    => list modified so that list[i][j][k]==val
2

2
  Mapping:
2
:map_prop    (obj-list,prop)            => list of o.(prop)          for all o
2
:map_verb    (obj-list,verb[,args])     => list of o:(verb)(@args)   for all o
2
:map_arg     ([n,]obj,verb,{x...},args) => list of o:(verb)(x,@args) for all x
2
:map_builtin (obj-list, funcname)       => list of funcname(o)       for all o
2

2
  Assocation lists (lists of 'tuples', or secondary lists):
2
:assoc        (targ,alist[,i]) => 1st tuple in alist whose i-th element is targ
2
:iassoc *     (targ,alist[,i]) => index of same.
2
:assoc_prefix (targ,alist[,i]) => ... whose i-th element has targ as a prefix
2
:iassoc_prefix(targ,alist[,i]) => index of same.
2
:iassoc_sorted(targ,slist[,i]) => index of last element in sortedlist <= targ
2
:slice             (alist[,i]) => list of i-th elements
2
:sort_alist *      (alist[,i]) => alist sorted on i-th elements.
2
:amerge  (alist,[tind,[dind]]) => merges tuples of alist with matching i-th elt
2
:build_alist          (list,N) => make an alist of N-intervals from list
2
:make_alist  (list, list, ...) => make an alist of paired elements from lists
2

2
  Special use:
2
:same_sets    (list1, list2)   => do lists contain identical elements?
2
:sort_cardinal_suspended(list) => sort list of exits, by direction
2

2
:group_objects (obj-list, parent-list1, parent-list2, ...)
2
    => {obj-list1, obj-list2, ..., unclassified-objs}
