You can customize your role-playing environment to your liking by setting your preferences. To see what's available, type:
2

2
  @prefs
2

2
You should see something like this:
2

2
    Preference        Value      Description
2
[ ansi            ]     1      | use ansi color
2
[ autofight       ]     1      | keep attacking once begun
2
[ map             ]     1      | add map to room descriptions
2
[ opendoors       ]     1      | open closed doors automatically as you walk
2
[ showexits       ]     1      | show exits in room descriptions
2
[ tersefight      ]     1      | reduce combat spam by not showing swings, etc
2
[ unlockdoors     ]     0      | unlock locked doors automatically if you have the key
2
[ weights         ]     1      | show weights of objects
2

2
Most preferences, and all of the ones shown, are 'on/off', or binary, preferences. You can toggle their value by typing:
2

2
   @pref <pref> is <on|off|1|0>
2

2
You can use 'on/off' or '1/0' notation when setting a preference.
