2
HOW PATHING WORKS.
2

2
When an NPC has to get from A to B, what happens?  Here's what doesn't happen: NPC calculates the path between A and B and then starts walking it.
2

2
Whaaa?
2

2
All paths in the game are pre-calculated.  That is, in every room, data is stored on which direction to go to get to every other room in the area.  This data is kept in exit.next_hops -- a list of all rooms reachable through that exit.  $area:recalc_next_hops() populates this data, using a breadth-first tree search (or however you say it, I'm not a rocket scientist).  This only happens on a manual area reset.
2

2
When an NPC needs to get to B, he calls room:next_hop_to(OBJ B) on his current location.  This returns an exit -- or #-1 if that room isn't reachable from here.
2

2
You can check pathing from a location with '@pathto <dest>'.  If a path goes through an exit it shouldn't, you can set exit.next_hop_ok = 0.  This tells recalc_next_hops not to use this exit as a path to anywhere.  NOTE: cliffs are .next_hop_ok=0 by default.
2

2
AREA TRANSITIONS
2

2
What if the dest is in a different area?  When pathing is calculated, exits from the area into a new area have that new area put into their .next_hops, as if it were a room.  So every room in an area has every area connected to this area, somewhere in one of its exits .next_hops.  If you're in slagtown and need to get to a room in freedom city, here:next_hop_to() looks for freedom city (#327) in .next_hops of its exits.
2

2
What if the dest area isn't adjacent to this area?  The region's .map_area is used.  This is a special area ('earth map' for earth) kept outside of time, with one room for each area in the region.  These rooms are connected by exits, in a map analogous to the actual area-adjacency connections of the actual areas in the region.  So when :next_hop_to() needs to find a hop to a non-adjacent area, it basically asks the region map for an area-next-hop between the two areas.  Say you were going from slagtown to Any Port.  In the region map, the next area-hop from slagtown to AP is freedom city.  So it would then look for the next hop from here to freedom city (which IS an adjacent area).  Got all that?
2

2
Mostly you don't have to worry about the integrity of this map; the rooms are autogenerated and auto-linked as they're built and reset.  If you're ever in doubt or feel like you've been screwing with the global architecture too much, 'ascend' into the clouds and @reset-area on the region's map area.
2

