 -- MOO v1.9.0 (Hell variant): new help topics --
2
 
2
 See "help <topic>" for more information:
2

2
Overview topics: 
2
  hashintro      -- new data type, a fast associative array.
2
  hashes         -- short version of the above.
2
  yield          -- new language statement: conditionally suspend.
2
  
2
Functions:
2
  hash()         -- make hashes out of lists
2
  hashremove()   -- delete entries from a hash
2
  optimize()     -- shrink a hash's memory footprint
2
  keys()         -- list of hash keys
2
  values()       -- list of hash values
2

2
(Wizards can also check 'help wizchanges'.)
29
5
4
15
2
yield: conditional suspending
2

2
You're probably familiar with our old friend, $cu:sin, aka $command_utils:suspend_if_needed.
2
This has been, historically, one of the most called verbs on the MOO -- i.e., 15,000 times a 
2
second. To help us code more straightforwardly, without the overhead of verb calls, we now
2
have a new keyword in MOO code: "yield".
2

2
Here is an example of how to use it:
2
  for x in [1 .. 250000]
2
    yield;
2
  endfor
2

2
If the task has less than 1000 ticks, or 1 second of execution time remaining, yield will
2
suspend the task for 1 second. (These defaults can be changed in the server's options.h file, 
2
and therefore require a recompliation to change.)
