2
Syntax:   optimize   ( HASH a_hash ) => HASH
2

2
  Returns a copy of a_hash which may use less space in memory than 
2
  the original version did. Unfortunately, as of 1.9.0, there is
2
  no way of actually telling if optimize() did anything.
2
  
2
  Generally this only would be useful on a hash which is stored
2
  in a property that has shrunk in size past a threshold of 
2
  (75% of any power of 2 larger than 16).
2
  
2
  (e.g. shrinking smaller than 24, 48, 96, 192, 384, 768, ...)
2

2
Errors:
2
  E_TYPE:   if a_hash isn't a hash.
