2
first_in(OBJ an_object) => OBJ first object in its contents
2
last_in(OBJ an_object) => OBJ last object in its contents
2

2
first_child(OBJ an_object) => OBJ first object that is its child
2
first_child(OBJ an_object) => OBJ last object that is its child
2

2
  All four of these functions have the same result as getting the full
2
list of contents or children and getting the first or last element of that list. But these functions are much, much faster.
2

2
  Added in version 1.10.4 (May 15, 2010).
