2
Control Room
29
5
2
Dim light reflects off the bronzed surfaces of control panels here, revealing an array of needle-tipped gauges, analog counters, round-button panels, and long-handled levers. Several marine-style steering wheels are lined up along one wall. Blasts of steam occasionally pour forth from tall pipes in one corner. You can hear the quiet clicking and whirring of gears and counters, and an irregular metallic clang echoes up from below. The air is slightly damp and warm.
