2
It's a weapon -- that's right, you can kill people with it.  If you're holding it (try 'hold <name of weapon>'), you'll be using it when you attack someone with 'attack <person/creature/helpless orphan'.  Note that if you're NOT holding it, you WON'T be using it when you attack -- you'll be using your fists or, god forbid, that fluffy pillow you were holding.  You can find out what you're holding with 'inventory' (or just 'i') -- held things are marked as such.
2

2
Curious which weapons are better than others?  Try 'gear', you'll get all kinds of statistics about the weapons in your inventory.
2

2
Some weapons can be 'dual wielded', that is, you can hold two of them.  You can tell which by, again, looking at 'gear'.  This will give you a penalty to hit, but you'll be dealing out more attacks faster.
