2
REGARDING THE SKILLS THAT PAY THE BILLS:
2

2
Skills are an important part of HellMOO. Without them, we would never rise above the simple existance of crank-snorting AIDS infected landshrimps. HellMOO offers a cornucopia of hot-'n-sticky skills, which will be covered later, but first it is important to go over how they work.
2

2
You can see what skills you have by using the 'score' command, or 'sc'.  This will show you your skills and also your stats, which affect your skills. ( To see just one skill, type 'sc <skillname>'. )  The first column after the skill's name is the RAW score, or how much you have learned in that partictular skill. By using skills, your RAW skill will occasionally rise by 0.01 points, which uses an Improvement Point (IP).
2

2
The next column is the Total skill value, which is the number used when calculating the effeciency of using your skills. The Total takes into factor not just how much you have learned and the value of your RAW score, but also your stats and anything which may effect them, like drugs, implants, or stress. Next to Total is the + column, which lets you know about other conditions changing your total skill score, such as getting a bonus to Fuck from being super horny, or getting a penalty to Climb from that compound fracture in your arm.
2

2
Next up is the Depends column, which tells you what stat is needed for what skill - the higher those stats, the higher your Total score will be. Additionally, skill-dependant stats will also rise by 0.01 by using the skill that they depend on. Your stats will grow very slowly through use of skills and Improvement Points, while growth of certain skills may be rapid, especially early on.
2

2
Finally is the Improve column, which lets you know how expensive it will be to improve a skill through training. By training, you can raise the RAW point of a skill by one point, and forego trying to improve it by using the skill. Hard work is for suckers. As your RAW points become higher in a certain skill, the cost of improving them by trainers will increase also. Training your first RAW point in a skill might be as little as 400 XP, while training a skill with a RAW score of 10 may be over 10,000 XP, so you better get started on smashing some orphan skull as soon as you're done reading this.
2

2
Finding people to teach you skills is fuckin easy, shitpile. Ask around, as some players are able to teach skills, and will probably do so in exchange for sexual favors. If you favor your dignity, you can either find a different MOO, or pay an NPC to train you instead. There are NPC trainers all over the place that teach pretty much every skill, but they charge for it - the amount of dough needed is the same as the amount of XP needed to train that skill. If you need to know where these trainers are, check out the telephone pole on the 600 block of High Street in Freedom City, there are flyers posted.
2

2
Having a 0 raw skill sucks hard - you get a huge penalty to your Total score for it, so find somebody to teach you up to at least 1 if you want to use that skill. You're going to want to have a Climb skill of around 10 or 11 if you don't want exploring HellMOO to turn into a gross, frusturating misadventure.  Some skills are used automatically when attacking, swimming or driving, and some are used manually when you invoke a certain command.
2

2
For more information on a skill, refer to 'help <skill>'.
361
5
4
51
2
Basic movement -- the eight compass directions, up/down, and in/out -- is as simple as typing the direction you want to go (or just a single letter -- 'w' for west, 'u' for up, etc). However, you can't really walk willy-nilly, since like in real life you can't walk through walls. Although that would be totally awesome. So how do you know where the hell you can go? Check the bottom of the room description for a location. Here's one for Fourth Ave - 500 Block:
2

2
[ Exits: north south east(door) west ]
2

2
You can go 'north', 'south', 'east', or 'west' here. East can also be reached by typing 'door'. Occasionally you may need to type the more detailed direction to specify. The star next to east means the pathway is closed. In some cases, like this, you can simply open it and head through, but occasionally it's locked.
2

2
East is hilighted in blue. What the hell does that mean? It means you're about to go to a new area. Look at the top of the location description.
2

2
Fourth Ave - 500 block (freedom city) 6:43pm
2

2
Pretty simple. We're at Fourth Ave - 500 block in Freedom City at 6:43pm.
2

2
This MOO has a map, thank GOD. You can see it whenever you head to a new location -- it's embedded in the room description. Once again at Fourth Ave - 500 Block:
2

2
====##====
2
AP||CLAN
2
Re()<=.
2
420||. Am
2
CP==##====
2

2
The minimap has a 5x5 block range with you in the middle, the blue (). You can see abbreviations for various buildings and locations. At night, it's just black and white, which can be confusing if you're in a new place after dark.
2

2
Wanna see more? You have a wristpad in your inventory, and since you have it, you can use 'map' to see a larger area.
2

2
| . ||. . ??||. . HP||. ||[]
2
[]| . ||BH. RT||BCCS. ||MB||.
2
======##======##======##==##BS
2
*. SG||CR. AP||CLAN$$||Th||.
2
[]. . ||. Re(). . . ||Sm||.
2
*[]PZ||. 420||. AmPr||CA||.
2
==##==##==CP==##======##IE||WW
2
||. . . VC||SUGS[]EO==####
2
.. . . [] . ||CS. []. *.....
2

2
Now that's a damn fine map! If that's not enough, try 'lmap' for a more detailled map complete with legend (spammy map not pictured here).
2

2
If you wanna look somewhere before you walk onto it to help avoid RoboRapist3000, use 'look <direction>' to see where you're going, if you're capable of looking there. You can't look through, say, a closed door.
2

2
While you're running around like a horrible radioactive lunatic (you are), watch out for the red directions. Those mean you may have to climb, and climbing, swimming, and all that can make for some pretty good times.
2

2
If you're getting tired of moving with your legs alone, there are a wide variety of vehicles (and at least a couple mutations) that can make your movement faster. These range from motorcycles for the land, ultralight helicopters to zeppelins for the sky, and speedboats up to party yachts for the sea. See 'help travel' for more information.
2

2
---
2
Summary:
2
- Compass directions, in/out, up/down make up basic movement
2
- Type a direction to go there (single letters!)
2
- Use the map and look around to see where you are and where you're going
2
- 'map' and 'lmap' let you see more of your surroundings
2
- You may have to climb, swim, or fall
2
 - 'help travel' for vehicle information
2

