There are a number of options to change your gameplay experience, accessible via the '@prefs' command. Type '@prefs' to see a list of options and your current settings for them.
2

2
Most prefs are self-explanatory, or at least simple enough that the single-line description can explain them. Some of the more esoteric options are described below.
2

2
- ansihack -- Some MOO clients don't respond to certain ANSI (color) codes. If you notice that colors seem to be leaking (things are bold when they aren't supposed to be, things are inconsistently colored, etc.,) turn this on to see if it helps.
2
- singlecolumn -- This changes your inventory listing, and the list of contents of containers, so that each item appears on a line by itself, rather than the default two-per-line display.
2

2
To adjust a preference, use '@prefs <preference> is <value>'. For example, '@prefs map is 0'. (Note: Not recommended. The map is very handy.)
