2
When you encounter bugs in the game, we respectfully ask that you report them. Any the fabric of the world has ruptured sort of message is an obvious bug, but there are other more subtle bugs that don't generate an error but still need to be reported. This is especially important if you find an exploit... something in the game that allows you to gain money, experience, or other game benefits faster than should normally be possible. Basically, if it seems too good to be true, it probably is and should be reported to an admin.
2

2
To report bugs, use the '@qsend' command to send a message to the *bugs mailing list, as shown below. When you are finished typing your report, enter a period (dot) character on a line by itself to send the message.  Or you can simply put the whole message on the same line with the command:
2

2
'@qsend *bugs When you open the bottle of champagne the cork doesn't pop and also you get AIDS'
2

2
You will also be asked to attach things to your report. To do this, type '@attach <thing> to <number> on *bugs'. For example, in the above case, you would do something like this:
2

2
'@attach bottle to $ on *bugs' (note: $ means the last post on a list, if you just made a bug report then yours will most certainly be the last)
2

2
You can also attach a room by typing '@attach here to <number> on *bugs'. Please make sure to attach any relevant objects to your bug reports! Sending in a vague report with no objects attached will make the admins very angry!
