2
A piece of clothing (or armor) covers certain areas of your body, and probably doesn't cover certain others. This means you'll need several pieces to cover your entire body, if that's your goal. To see what's covering what, try the command 'worn'.
2

2
Similarly, it protects against certain types of damage, and probably doesn't protect against certain others. To see what's protecting against what, try the command 'gear'.
2

2
You can wear one piece of clothing over another, up to a point. The thickness (shown by 'worn') of a piece of armor controls how much more you can wear along with it on the same body part -- thicknesses on one part can't stack up to more than your Brawn, or 15, whichever is lower.
2

2
Clothing takes damage when you're attacked; if it takes enough, it'll disintegrate. You can repair your clothing with 'repair <item>', using your repair skill.
2

2
Looking for clothing?  There's a donation bin in the orphanage basement.  Or try Threads (Th on your minimap) for something a little nicer, or Protect Ya Neck (Pr on your minimap) for something with actual armor to it.
361
5
4
9
2
We all gotta eat. Eating satisfies your hunger (check your hunger level with the 'st' command), and helps you heal up from damage if you're sitting down.
2

2
There are many sources of food available, of widely varying quality. The cheapest option is to simply butcher meat from your dead victims (try 'butcher from <corpse>' ). However, raw meat isn't all that nutritious, it rots quickly, and it can give you worms, or a nasty infection.
2

2
The next option is to buy food. You can get a decent meal at several restaurants in FC and a few places in the hinterlands as well. This can get expensive over time, but you'll almost always feel safe eating. Try Jack n Wendy's in the north side of FC.
2

2
Another option is soylent -- yeah, you know what it's made of. Drag a corpse to the Recycling Center in FC, jam it into the RDCD unit, and for $1 you've got a bar of nutritious, long-lasting soylent.
2

2
Perhaps the best option is to cook food yourself, or make friends with a good cook. You can buy a cookbook at the bookstore, and a cooking stove at the hardware store, and turn disgusting chudmeat into a delicious gourmet meal! Home cooked food is nutritious, resistant to rot, and most importantly, eating it will reduce your stress.
361
5
4
7
2
Crafting is a great way to get some unique and rare items. It's also great for building up a stock of ammunition (some guns ammo is only available through crafting), for making drugs, and for cooking delicious food.
2

2
To craft, you need three things -- a workbench, a recipe, and some ingredients. There are several different workbenches, each of which can make particular kinds of recipes (cooking stoves make food recipes, electronics benches make electronics, etc.). There are a few exceptions to this rule, recipes which don't actually require a workbench and can be made in the field -- 'examine' any recipes you find if you think they might be of this type.
2

2
If you're interested in learning more, invest in some kind of workbench and read the help on it to find out exactly how it works.  Or if you can't afford that, you could try to improvise something.
2

2
See also: help improvise
