Weapons gradually degrade through use -- every time you score a hit with one, there's a chance it will degrade. After some amount of damage, it will become less accurate, slower, and less damaging. You'll see these changes happen in gear if you're paying close attention.
2

2
Q: Will my weapons break and vanish on me?! I killed people to get that damn thing!
2

2
A: Yes.  Keep your weapons in good condition!  Or use disposable weapons.
2

2
Q: Will the weapon be permanently fucked up by repair, like armor?
2

2
A: No. You can always repair it back to its factory-fresh condition.
2

2
Q: How hard is it to repair a weapon?
2

2
A: It varies, based on the value of the weapon and the number of mods. Guns are also
2
slightly harder to repair than melee.
2

2
Q: How can I see my weapon's health?
2

2
A: You can't see the exact value, but you can look at the weapon and get an idea of its
2
condition. If it doesn't mention the condition, it's at or near full health.
