2
IS MY APARTMENT SAFE?
2

2
So you've bought an apartment and you're merrily squirreling away your precious loots. But you wonder...am I really safe? Could rapist murderer thieves break in here in the middle of the night and clean out my cabinets, rape my e-wife, have a cigarette, then flip her over and go in for seconds?
2

2
The short answer: possibly.
2

2
Your apartment is at risk of being broken into if any of the following are true:
2

2
- You're logged in.
2
- You're logged out, but NOT sleeping in your apartment.
2
- You're logged out, but other people are awake INSIDE your apartment.
2
- Anyone scanned into your apartment lock is awake.
2
- You were dumb and installed your lock on the wrong side of your door.
2

2
If none of those are true -- that is, you are logged off, inside your apartment, no roommates are awake, and nobody else is awake in there -- you're safe from a break-in. For those times when you're NOT safe, you'll want a good lock on your door, the best you can afford, and possibly even some countermeasures if you can afford them. In most cases, the lock that comes with your apartment isn't that good.
2

2
What if I'm home and someone starts picking my lock?  You can't log out to escape -- it's too late.  The best you can probably do is to pull out a gun, get in cover and start aiming at the door.  Better call in some heavy duty friends, or set up a quick explosive trap...
2

2
See also: help rent
