2
If you don't have your health, what DO you have?
2

2
Health is precious. You've got a bar full of it (type 'st' to see it). When people beat on you, or you fall off a cliff, or starve, or get irradiated, or whatever -- you'll lose health. When it hits zero, you'll die.
2

2
How do you get it back? Several ways, in order of decreasing convenience:
2

2
- Use a nanite healer. (Takes a little medic skill)
2
- Use a trauma kit. (Takes more medic skill)
2
- Have sex or eat food, then sit or lie down for a while. (Can be slow)
2

2
You can even increase your maximum health through the use of endocrine boosters, buyable in the corpclave.
2

2
See also: help illness, help medic
361
5
4
27
2
When it comes to beating the shit out of people, you have quite a few things going for you. For one, beating the shit out of people is a fun, enjoyable, and usually profitable activity on many levels. For two, you have quite a few choices on HOW to beat the shit out of somebody.
2

2
That doesn't mean you should grab the nearest leg and go at it, however. There are a few things you should keep in mind before picking weapons, and this guide will help you find the ultimate shit-beating device for you and you alone.
2

2
Let's go over the basic types of weaponry:
2

2
'Blades' - Blades are a simple weapon, and usually do either slash or stab damage. They may cause your opponent to bleed. Blades rely on your reflexes and cool. Blades also have a secondary usage of cutting skin, meat, and other delicious organs off dead bodies.
2

2
'Clubs' - The shit-beaters for when you want to BEAT the shit out of somebody. Clubs are all brawn and reflexes, and can also break limbs if you have a good one. Sledgehammers, pipes, and spoons are all clubs, giving you a bit of choice in weaponry.
2

2
'Fists' - Of course, hand-to-hand combat is always a choice. This relies on your brawn and endurance. Your bare fists aren't exactly the best, so buy some knuckles. Of course, if you step into the right radiation...
2

2
'Pistols' - Shoot some shit. Pistols can do shot/bullet damage, cause somebody to bleed or go in shock, and rely on cool and reflexes. Of course, you need to carry a healthy supply of ammo if you want to go on a longer expedition. And make sure the ammo matches the gun!
2

2
'Rifles' - Shotguns, AKs, and the other large guns. Like pistols, these require ammo and do shot/bullet damage and are generally nasty to deal with. They're rather heavy and take a great deal of practice, but in the right hands are insanely powerful. They take cool and reflexes.
2

2
'Spears' - An unorthodox weapon that relies on endurance and reflexes. That weird stat pairing suggests weaker characters can still use spears effectively. Unfortunately, there's not many spear weapons to go around.
2

2
'Whips' - Kinky. Relies on your reflexes and senses. Can do a plethora of damage types, depending on the whip you're using. Is effective for uncool, unbrawny types.
2

2
So which weapon should you use? That comes down to your personal preference, and your stats. If you're an agile, cool fucker, you have quite a few choices going for you. If you're a tough, enduring fucker, go with fist weapons. If you have the right skill for a weapon, you may want to go with that, or take up a whole new type if your stats don't match well. Experiment.
2

2
Never forget that not all weapons are equal. A certain blade may stab enemies, while another may slash. When fighting enemies, take note of what damage type hurts hardest, and maximize that how you can.
2

2
If you're holding several different weapons, type 'gear' to see a readout of all your weapons and armor. For weapons, this will tell such things as the raw skill range needed, your speed and to-hit with a weapon, and the damage you'll do with it. (Read 'help gear' for more information about this display.)
2

2
Of course, if you have the brains to, or know a friend, you can always buy some mods and deck out your weapon with sweet-ass enhancements. A laser sight is always nice on a gun, and who wouldn't want a butane flame sword? Experiment and beat the shit out of some orphans, effectively!
361
5
4
13
2
So you've probably spent a little time walking around Hell and figured, "God damn this place is huge, there's got to be easier ways to get around." Well, wonder no more, for there are various forms of maneuvering about in the world. From things like skateboarding down the street, roaring down the road with your motorcycle, flying the skies in your plane, or shoving relative theory in every physicist's face with teleportation.
2

2
You're excited to try these fancy things out now, I'm sure. However, there are various things you must know before you take any of these in mind -
2

2
Riding - Skateboards and Motorcycles, hot damn! This is your quicker form of terrain motion, dependant on your Ride skill, which takes being cool and having some reflexes to work properly. If you're apprehensive of getting on that board or riding off in the wind without any knowledge, it's rumored that Suzie used to be a mad drag queen in her youth. Otherwise, there are various halfpipes around Hell on which you can practice your riding abilities.
2

2
Flying - They look like ants from up here, don't they? All sorts of crazy planes and a special mutation exist to allow you to traverse the skies. Bucko and Alexis offer a fine piloting service for a nominal fee, depending on where you'd like to go. They have beacons set up on helipads spread around Hell, if you flip one on they'll arrive to take you anywhere in a flash. With some pilot skill, you could fly your own plane. Brains and Reflexes are what help you be a better pilot, and as for acquiring your own plane, Corpclave's local aeromarket Simon & Simon will sell you a Cessna and insurance for a fair $56,000. The Cessna tiltrotor isn't the cheapest plane, though, nor is it the fastest or biggest; in fact, scientists have researched plans for all sorts of planes, including even zeppelins. Ask around and see if you can find someone who knows how to build one. You can also develop the ability to fly on your own, but it's cold out there, so bring a cloak. There are also crazy monsters flying around, and you're not safe from them outside of your cozy little plane. Keep your eyes peeled.
2

2
Teleportation - There are a couple of mutations out there that give you the ability to teleport, one of them gives near-free teleportation. Your focus skill, which relies on your endurance and senses, is what determines how well this ability works. Focusing on a place and then teleporting to it is much harder than you would think, and you could very well end up in some radioactive wasteland or worse, exploding when you try. Take great caution when exercising this power!
2

2
Boats - It used to be that the Gulf of Stockton wasn't really worth traveling, and it was only sailed by a single band of pirates. Nowadays shipwrights are back in work building and restoring boats for your use. If you head out west to Botany Bay, there's a store there that'll let you be the captain of your own vessel. For a mere $24,750, they'll set you up with a cheap one-room runabout. They've got a few bigger boats too, all the way up to gas-guzzling luxury yachts for over $500K. There aren't currently any craftable boats, but there's a pretty nice graphical map at http://hellmoo.org/~dionysus/boats/ that will show you the entire Gulf as well as all the boats and islands on it.
2

2
Remember my horribly mutated friend, your ability to go places and make things happen is limited only by your desire to do so.
