Most multi-word commands are of two forms:
2

2
<verb> <object>
2
'fuck larry'
2
'kill me'
2

2
or:
2

2
<verb> <object> <preposition> <indirect-object>
2
'inject larry with heroin'
2
'get knife from cabinet'
2

2
If you exam places or things, you'll see what commands (if any) are obviously available on it.
2

2
If there's more than one of something, you might want to refer to a specific instance:
2

2
'get fourth cheese grater'
2
'drop 4.grater'
2
'get 4th grater'
2

2
Sometimes you'll want to refer to several things of the same name in one command, usually when getting or dropping things in a room or a container. Just use the all modifier. Try things like:
2

2
'get all'
2
'drop all potato'
2
'put all grenade in cake'
2

2
You can also refer to whole categories of objects:
2

2
'get all artifacts from case'
2
'put all clothing in wardrobe'
2
'get all food from fridge'
2

2
Possible categories:
2
weapon (aka weapons)
2
ammo
2
clothes (aka clothing, armor, cloth)
2
medical (aka med)
2
foods (aka food, consumables)
2
artifacts (aka artifact, art)
2
containers
2
trophies (aka trophy)
2
recipes (aka recipe)
2
parts (aka part)
2
chemicals (aka chemical, chem)
