2
There are several ways to see a visual map of your immediate surroundings.
2

2
The most obvious is just 'look', or 'l' for short. You'll see a mini-map in the upper left corner of your current location's description. Each square of the minimap represents one location.
2

2
For a wider view, 'map' will show you a larger map with more locations. If you have a GPS unit, you can use it to get an even wider version of this view.
2

2
For a more detailed view, 'lmap' will show you locations surrounding your current position, along with lines showing obvious exits, and an annotated legend explaining what each location is.
2

2
In all maps, the ~1b[44m~1b[36m~1b[1m()~1b[0m~1b[36m in the middle represents your location.
