2
The 'grab <creature>' command lets you try to throw your arms around someone (or something) and restrain it. While you're restraining someone, you'll still be able to do things like attack, but they'll be helpless! This means you can do things to them you wouldn't normally be allowed to do, like fuck them. You can also use the otherwise ineffective 'shove <creature> to <direction>' command while you are restraining someone, allowing you to push someone through an unobstructed exit, as long as the exit isn't above your current location.
2

2
Your success at grabbing is based on your brawn and reflexes, whereas your target defends with its dodge. Once you've grabbed them, it's your brawn versus their brawn and reflexes.
2

2
If you've been grabbed, there isn't much you can do about it but wait for your strength and reflexes to overcome your opponent and break you free. You can make yourself harder to grab by getting covered in oil (or some other slippery fluid), or with certain mutations.
