2
The 'search' command lets you search your current location for hidden or salvageable items. It uses scavenge skill; the higher your scavenge total, the more likely you are to find good loot.
2

2
Different items are found in different places; explore thoroughly and search in different types of locations repeatedly to see what you can turn up. With enough searching in one location, you will eventually exhaust it, and have to move on to a new spot for a while.
2

2
Some locations may have special hidden clues, items, or doors -- you'll often get a hint when entering such a room. Keep searching in that spot until you've found the secret. If you just can't find it, you might need to train up your scavenge skill and come back.
2

2
Scavenging is a great way to make cash when you're just starting out, and for craft and science it's absolutely essential throughout your career. Most ingredients and components in the game are found via scavenging.
