2
[ You earned 1 IP in reading help! ]
2

2
Ha, not really. What's an IP? IP stands for Improvement Point. Let's look at a line from the 'sc' display:
2

2
repair 2.57 [11] Brn 840xp Simple engine repairs.
2

2
That .57 after the 2 raw means 57 IP. When you've gained 100 IP, your raw skill bumps up by 1 and IP resets to 0.
2

2
You gain IP in a skill by using that skill -- when fishing, you'll gain fish IP. IP gain happens most often when you're doing a somewhat challenging task; very easy (or very difficult) things are less likely to give you IP. This process of finding tasks at your skill level to earn you IP is often called grinding.  Note that it will cost you a few XP when you earn an IP, usually 1 to 10; if you don't have any XP to spend, you can't earn IP at all.
2

2
You can only gain a certain number of IP every game day. The sc display will show how many IP you can still earn today. The more IP you've earned out of your daily total, the more each IP will tend to cost you in XP.
