There are lots of ways to communicate in Hell. The simplest is just talking:
2

2
'say Hey there friendly people!'
2

2
You can abbreviate say with a doublequote character. You can also talk directly to someone with a dash character:
2

2
'-kharn Hi Kharn! Please stop murdering me!'
2

2
You can talk to someone far away by using your wristpad, with the page command:
2

2
'page kharn Why did you cut my head off and rape the stump?'
2
'page help Kharn has cut off my head nine times now, advise plz thx!'
2
'page huck I just saw Kharn in the orphanage'
2

2
You can also use emotes (see help emote) :
2

2
':cries and begs for mercy.'
2
'.kiss huck's feet'
2

2
 and mail (see help mail) :
2

2
'@qsend huck Thanks man, I owe you one!'
2

2
If you want to learn more about another player in an automated way, you can try 'smalltalk <player>'.  If they agree, you'll have a bit of a chat about your various skills and fetishes.
2

2
To check out the chat networks available on your wristpad, see help nets.
2
To check out the mailing lists players can use, see help mail.
