You can control what you allow other players to do to you with the ~1b[1m~1b[37mallows~1b[22m~1b[36m command. Try just typing ~1b[1m~1b[37mallows~1b[22m~1b[36m by itself. You'll see a list of what you do and don't allow other people to do.
2

2
You can allow a particular person by name (or simply ~1b[1mfriends~1b[22m (see: ~1b[1mhelp~1b[22m friends) or everyone) to do the following kinds of things to you:
2

2
~1b[1mcocoon~1b[22m - Let them open your ~1b[1mcocoon.~1b[22m (see ~1b[1mhelp~1b[22m cocoons)
2
gifts - Let them ~1b[1mgive~1b[22m you things.
2
