Supply any of their needs and they'll usually pay you. If you prefer not to ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m an honest buck, you can always try running a ~1b[1mscam~1b[22m on someone.
2

2
You can ~1b[1mscavenge~1b[22m for loot to sell -- this can be quite profitable early in the game. Check the crack mansion, Sharpton Projects, gangland, the sewers, and many other locations until you've found the best spots.
2

2
Upstairs in Any Port is Fat Ratzo. Fat, ugly, and probably piggy, but he's got ~1b[1mjobs~1b[22m for you. Ask him about jobs; he could always use someone to deliver packages, and there're always some (possibly easy) ~1b[1mbounties~1b[22m to ~1b[1mkill~1b[22m for good cash.
2

2
Or take a job with the ENEMA ~1b[1mcorp.~1b[22m ~1b[1mMServo~1b[22m hangs out at the ~1b[1mmuseum~1b[22m and is happy to hire any new players.
2

2
Of course, you're not limited to just these methods. Go ahead, check out the town. You never know. (But you can't steal cash, [un]fortunately.)
