In any post-apocalyptic scenario, there will be violence and bloodshed. Guess what? Now YOU get to be a part of the action! Of course, if you don't wanna die, then you might wanna know a few things about HellMOO's combat.
2

2
In HellMOO, there are numerous things that determine the outcome of battle: your combat ~1b[1mskills~1b[22m and equipment, the enemy combat capabilities, the ~1b[1mdodge~1b[22m factors of both parties involved, how many are attacking who, ~1b[1mstatus~1b[22m inflictions, etc. It's not terribly complicated, really! I swear!
2

2
The first thing you want to do before ~1b[1mfighting~1b[22m somebody (or something) is to appraise them. To do so, type:
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mapp <target>~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
Replace <target> with what you're appraising. This will ~1b[1mgive~1b[22m you an idea of whether or not you can ~1b[1mkill~1b[22m them. (Of course, some enemies won't even bother waiting and will ~1b[1mattack~1b[22m first, but that's something else.)
2

2
Now, do you still want to ~1b[1mkill~1b[22m them? Okay.
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mattack~1b[22m <target>~1b[22m~1b[36m (or) ~1b[1m~1b[37mk <target>~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
When attacking an enemy, you'll see some fancy red text that shows you the beginning and end of battles. You'll swing your weapon at them, and they'll swing their weapon at you. You will use whatever you have in your hand as a weapon, including non-weapons, such as junk you picked up, trauma kits, etc. These non-weapons will count as fist attacks, so unless you specialize in fists, ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m sure you have a weapon equipped (preferably one you're good at using) before you engage in combat!
2

2
Attacks are shown by brackets and a description of ~1b[1mattack,~1b[22m in this format:
2

2
[C###m] The mangy dog's eyes glaze over as Casull's slam bat makes a gaping hole in its back!
2

2
In the example, C in the brackets represents the attacker, m in the brackets represents the target, and the # in the middle represent damage. All damage indicators are red. A is minor damage, a * is medium damage, and a # is major damage; in the example, I pretty much wasted that dog. Of course, not all attacks will connect:
2

2
[m)C] Casull smoothly dodges out of the mangy dog's bite.
2

2
In this case, the symbol in the middle represents something that happened that prevented damage to the target. There are numerous symbols, but all you need to know is that, for some reason or other, the target did not get it. If the target is you, huzzah! If the target is your enemy, not so huzzah.
2

2
If you think the enemy's too difficult for you to ~1b[1mkill,~1b[22m and you already attacked it (or it attacked you) then you can attempt to run by moving in any direction that's available to you. You will either get away or you won't.
2

2
A battle will end in one of three different ways: Your enemy dies, you die, or you run away. If your enemy dies, you will get various amounts of ~1b[1mXP,~1b[22m unless HellMOO considers the enemy too easy for you. In that case, you get no ~1b[1mXP~1b[22m at all.
2

2
If you die...refer to the ~1b[1mhelp~1b[22m file on ~1b[1mDeath.~1b[22m Bring nanites and try to use them so that you don't die.
2

2
If you run away, congratulations, you're a non-dead coward! Heal yourself and keep running if the enemy was too hard. Or go ~1b[1mfight~1b[22m it again once you're fully healed; enemies usually can't heal themselves.
2

2
Summary:
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Battling is fun
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m ~1b[1m~1b[37mapp <target>~1b[22m~1b[36m before ~1b[1mfighting~1b[22m them to ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m sure you'll be fine
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m [C###m] is the battle system
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Various things factor in battle
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m ~1b[1mHold~1b[22m your weapon before you ~1b[1mfight~1b[22m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Run by moving away from the target in any direction
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Win a battle, get ~1b[1mXP,~1b[22m unless the enemy was too easy.
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Lose a battle, you die
2
~1b[1m~1b[37m *~1b[22m~1b[36m Run, heal, try again, enemies don't heal by themselves (usually)
2

