Congratulations! You have just died somehow, either because someone killed you, you killed yourself, a disease wiped you, etc. The question is, now what?
2

2
Well, I hope you first updated your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m before you died. Think of updating your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m as saving your game: If you die, your character goes back to that point. When you first start in HellMOO, you have a ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m already created for you, so if you die, you won't go back to the Dream World. How convenient!
2

2
Of course, you want to keep your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m updated as often as possible. A good idea to ~1b[1mupdate~1b[22m your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m is when you've used all your available ~1b[1mIP~1b[22m for the day, when you get a major ~1b[1mXP~1b[22m boost from killing a lot of enemies, before you go exploring-yeah, like I said, keeping your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m updated is a good idea. Of course, it costs ~1b[1mmoney~1b[22m to keep your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m updated, and that cost rises as you gain ~1b[1mXP.~1b[22m (If it were free, I'd ~1b[1mupdate~1b[22m my ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m multiples times every visit from paranoia.) To ~1b[1mupdate~1b[22m yourself, go to ~1b[1mClone~1b[22m Arrangers (CA on the map) and type ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mupdate~1b[22m~1b[36m~1b[22m . Quick and easy.
2

2
Dying also costs money; to resurrect yourself, you have to pay double the cost of updating, along with 10XP, plus you revert back to your last-updated ~1b[1mclone.~1b[22m Fortunately, it's not so easy to die at higher levels, but the cost gets steeper. If you don't have enough ~1b[1mmoney~1b[22m to pay for resurrection, you simply pay for it with a higher ~1b[1mXP~1b[22m cost.
2

2
And that's why dying sucks, but it doesn't suck too hard if you ~1b[1mupdate~1b[22m often.
2

2
Death won't necessarily set you back completely...hell, you might not even have to ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m yourself. If you're lucky, someone will have seen you die, and they'll have a defibrillator on them, which can wake you up from your dead state. You won't be able to ~1b[1mpage~1b[22m anyone inside the afterworld, but you can use ~1b[1mchatnet~1b[22m or ~1b[1mcorpchat~1b[22m to revive you, assuming your body hasn't rotted yet. Just remember that using either of them can mean that someone will come to your body to loot your corpse. And people will do so. Use your judgement before you decide on ~1b[1mdoing~1b[22m that.
2

2
Finally, with the ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m arrangers, you can ~1b[1mdelete~1b[22m your ~1b[1mclone~1b[22m if you feel like starting your character over again. Just go to the ~1b[1mClone~1b[22m Arrangers, type ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mdelete~1b[22m~1b[36m,~1b[22m and die. Next ~1b[1mtime,~1b[22m you'll be in Dreams of Before.
2

