REGARDING THE SKILLS THAT PAY THE BILLS:
2

2
Skills are an important part of HellMOO. Without them, we would never rise above the simple existance of crank-snorting AIDS infected landshrimps. HellMOO offers a cornucopia of hot-'n-sticky skills, which will be covered later, but first it is important to go over how they work.
2

2
You can see what skills you have by using the ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mscore~1b[22m~1b[36m~1b[22m command, or ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37msc~1b[22m~1b[36m.~1b[22m This will show you your skills and also your ~1b[1mstats,~1b[22m which affect your skills. ( To see just one skill, type ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37msc~1b[22m <skillname>~1b[22m~1b[36m. ) The first column after the skill's name is the RAW ~1b[1mscore,~1b[22m or how much you have learned in that partictular skill. By using skills, your RAW skill will occasionally rise by 0.01 points, which uses an ~1b[1mImprovement~1b[22m Point (IP).
2

2
The next column is the Total skill value, which is the number used when calculating the effeciency of using your skills. The Total takes into factor not just how much you have learned and the value of your RAW ~1b[1mscore,~1b[22m but also your ~1b[1mstats~1b[22m and anything which may effect them, like ~1b[1mdrugs,~1b[22m ~1b[1mimplants,~1b[22m or ~1b[1mstress.~1b[22m Next to Total is the + column, which lets you know about other conditions changing your total skill ~1b[1mscore,~1b[22m such as getting a bonus to ~1b[1mFuck~1b[22m from being super ~1b[1mhorny,~1b[22m or getting a penalty to ~1b[1mClimb~1b[22m from that compound fracture in your arm.
2

2
Next up is the Depends column, which tells you what stat is needed for what skill - the higher those ~1b[1mstats,~1b[22m the higher your Total ~1b[1mscore~1b[22m will be. Additionally, skill-dependant ~1b[1mstats~1b[22m will also rise by 0.01 by using the skill that they depend on. Your ~1b[1mstats~1b[22m will grow very slowly through use of skills and ~1b[1mImprovement~1b[22m Points, while growth of certain skills may be rapid, especially early on.
2

2
Finally is the Improve column, which lets you know how expensive it will be to improve a skill through ~1b[1mtraining.~1b[22m By ~1b[1mtraining,~1b[22m you can raise the RAW point of a skill by one point, and forego trying to improve it by using the skill. Hard work is for suckers. As your RAW points become higher in a certain skill, the cost of improving them by trainers will increase also. ~1b[1mTraining~1b[22m your first RAW point in a skill might be as little as 400 ~1b[1mXP,~1b[22m while ~1b[1mtraining~1b[22m a skill with a RAW ~1b[1mscore~1b[22m of 10 may be over 10,000 ~1b[1mXP,~1b[22m so you better get started on smashing some ~1b[1morphan~1b[22m skull as soon as you're done reading this.
2

2
Finding people to teach you skills is fuckin easy, shitpile. Ask around, as some players are able to teach skills, and will probably do so in exchange for sexual favors. If you favor your dignity, you can either find a different MOO, or pay an NPC to train you instead. There are NPC trainers all over the place that teach pretty much every skill, but they charge for it - the amount of dough needed is the same as the amount of ~1b[1mXP~1b[22m needed to train that skill. If you need to know where these trainers are, check out the telephone pole on the 600 block of High Street in Freedom City, there are flyers posted.
2

2
Having a 0 raw skill sucks hard - you get a huge penalty to your Total ~1b[1mscore~1b[22m for it, so find somebody to teach you up to at least 1 if you want to use that skill. You're going to want to have a ~1b[1mClimb~1b[22m skill of around 10 or 11 if you don't want exploring HellMOO to turn into a gross, frusturating misadventure. Some skills are used automatically when attacking, swimming or driving, and some are used manually when you invoke a certain command.
2

2
For more information on a skill, refer to ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mhelp~1b[22m <skill>~1b[22m~1b[36m.
