Basic movement -- the eight compass directions, up/down, and in/out -- is as simple as typing the direction you want to go (or just a single letter -- ~1b[1m~1b[37mw~1b[22m~1b[36m for west, ~1b[1m~1b[37mu~1b[22m~1b[36m for up, etc). However, you can't really walk willy-nilly, since like in real life you can't walk through walls. Although that would be totally awesome. So how do you know where the hell you can go? Check the bottom of the room description for a location. Here's one for Fourth Ave - 500 Block:
2

2
[ Exits: north south east(door) west ]
2

2
You can go ~1b[1m~1b[37mnorth~1b[22m~1b[36m, ~1b[1m~1b[37msouth~1b[22m~1b[36m, ~1b[1m~1b[37meast~1b[22m~1b[36m, or ~1b[1m~1b[37mwest~1b[22m~1b[36m here. East can also be reached by typing ~1b[1m~1b[37mdoor~1b[22m~1b[36m. Occasionally you may need to type the more detailed direction to specify. The star next to east means the pathway is closed. In some cases, like this, you can simply open it and head through, but occasionally it's locked.
2

