Messages can substitute pronouns (and names) of the creatures and things involved in an action. The % sign is used, along with one or two letters, to describe exactly what should be substituted.
2

2
%n - player
2
%dn - the player
2
%in - a player
2
%s - subject (he / she / it)
2
%o - object (him / her / it)
2
%p - possessive (his / her / its)
2
%r - reflexive (himself / herself / itself)
2

2
Note that for the %d and %i forms, the or a/an still won't be printed if the message is ~1b[1mtalking~1b[22m about a proper-named player (or NPC).
2

2
%t - thing
2
%dt - the thing
2
%it - a thing
2

2
%d - direct object
2
%dd - the direct object
2
%id - a direct object
2
%ds - direct object, as subject (he / she / it)
2
%do - direct object, as object (him / her / it)
2
%dp - direct object, possessive (his / her / its)
2
%dr - direct object, reflexive (himself / herself / itself)
2

2
For the capitalized version of any pronoun sub, just capitalize the letter(s).
