If an exit is marked in red, it means you have to climb to go that way. By looking in that direction, you can ~1b[1mtell~1b[22m if it's a climb up or down, the distance of the climb, the difficulty of the climb, and whether or not there's a rope. If you decide you want to try the climb, just move in that direction normally and the climbing will begin.
