2
When it comes to beating the shit out of people, you have quite a few things going for you. For one, beating the shit out of people is a fun, enjoyable, and usually profitable activity on many levels. For two, you have quite a few choices on HOW to beat the shit out of somebody.
2

2
That doesn't mean you should ~1b[1mgrab~1b[22m the nearest leg and go at it, however. There are a few things you should keep in mind before picking weapons, and this guide will ~1b[1mhelp~1b[22m you find the ultimate shit-beating device for you and you alone.
2

2
Let's go over the basic types of weaponry:
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mBlades~1b[22m~1b[36m - Blades are a simple weapon, and usually do either slash or stab damage. They may cause your opponent to bleed. Blades rely on your reflexes and cool. Blades also have a secondary usage of cutting skin, meat, and other delicious organs off dead bodies.
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mClubs~1b[22m~1b[36m - The shit-beaters for when you want to BEAT the shit out of somebody. Clubs are all brawn and reflexes, and can also break limbs if you have a good one. Sledgehammers, pipes, and spoons are all clubs, giving you a bit of choice in weaponry.
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mFists~1b[22m~1b[36m - Of course, hand-to-hand ~1b[1mcombat~1b[22m is always a choice. This relies on your brawn and endurance. Your bare fists aren't exactly the best, so buy some knuckles. Of course, if you step into the right ~1b[1mradiation...~1b[22m
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mPistols~1b[22m~1b[36m - Shoot some shit. Pistols can do shot/bullet damage, cause somebody to bleed or go in shock, and rely on cool and reflexes. Of course, you need to carry a healthy supply of ammo if you want to go on a longer expedition. And ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m sure the ammo matches the gun!
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mRifles~1b[22m~1b[36m - Shotguns, AKs, and the other large guns. Like pistols, these require ammo and do shot/bullet damage and are generally nasty to deal with. They're rather heavy and take a great deal of ~1b[1mpractice,~1b[22m but in the right hands are insanely powerful. They take cool and reflexes.
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mSpears~1b[22m~1b[36m - An unorthodox weapon that relies on endurance and reflexes. That weird stat pairing suggests weaker characters can still use spears effectively. Unfortunately, there's not many spear weapons to go around.
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mWhips~1b[22m~1b[36m - Kinky. Relies on your reflexes and senses. Can do a plethora of damage types, depending on the whip you're using. Is effective for uncool, unbrawny types.
2

2
So which weapon should you use? That comes down to your personal preference, and your ~1b[1mstats.~1b[22m If you're an agile, cool fucker, you have quite a few choices going for you. If you're a tough, enduring fucker, go with fist weapons. If you have the right skill for a weapon, you may want to go with that, or take up a whole new type if your ~1b[1mstats~1b[22m don't match well. Experiment.
2

2
Never forget that not all weapons are equal. A certain blade may stab enemies, while another may slash. When ~1b[1mfighting~1b[22m enemies, take note of what damage type hurts hardest, and maximize that how you can.
2

2
If you're holding several different weapons, type ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mgear~1b[22m~1b[36m~1b[22m to see a readout of all your weapons and ~1b[1marmor.~1b[22m For weapons, this will ~1b[1mtell~1b[22m such things as the raw skill range needed, your speed and to-hit with a weapon, and the damage you'll do with it. (Read ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mhelp~1b[22m ~1b[1mgear~1b[22m~1b[36m~1b[22m for more information about this display.)
2

2
Of course, if you have the brains to, or know a friend, you can always buy some mods and deck out your weapon with sweet-ass enhancements. A laser sight is always nice on a gun, and who wouldn't want a butane flame sword? Experiment and beat the shit out of some orphans, effectively!
