Most multi-word ~1b[1mcommands~1b[22m are of two forms:
2

2
<verb> <object>
2
~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mfuck~1b[22m larry~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mkill~1b[22m me~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
or:
2

2
<verb> <object> <preposition> <indirect-object>
2
~1b[1m~1b[37minject larry with heroin~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget knife from cabinet~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
If you exam places or things, you'll see what ~1b[1mcommands~1b[22m (if any) are obviously available on it.
2

2
If there's more than one of something, you might want to refer to a specific instance:
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget fourth cheese grater~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mdrop 4.grater~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget 4th grater~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
Sometimes you'll want to refer to several things of the same name in one command, usually when getting or dropping things in a room or a container. Just use the all modifier. Try things like:
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget all~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mdrop all potato~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mput all grenade in cake~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
You can also refer to whole categories of objects:
2

2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget all artifacts from case~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mput all ~1b[1mclothing~1b[22m in wardrobe~1b[22m~1b[36m
2
~1b[1m~1b[37mget all ~1b[1mfood~1b[22m from fridge~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
Possible categories:
2
weapon (aka weapons)
2
ammo
2
~1b[1mclothes~1b[22m (aka ~1b[1mclothing,~1b[22m ~1b[1marmor,~1b[22m cloth)
2
medical (aka med)
2
foods (aka ~1b[1mfood,~1b[22m consumables)
2
artifacts (aka artifact, art)
2
containers
2
trophies (aka trophy)
2
~1b[1mrecipes~1b[22m (aka recipe)
2
parts (aka part)
2
chemicals (aka chemical, chem)
