There are several ways to see a visual map of your immediate surroundings.
2

2
The most obvious is just ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mlook~1b[22m~1b[36m,~1b[22m or ~1b[1m~1b[37ml~1b[22m~1b[36m for short. You'll see a mini-map in the upper left corner of your current location's description. Each square of the minimap represents one location.
2

2
For a wider view, ~1b[1m~1b[37mmap~1b[22m~1b[36m will show you a larger map with more locations. If you have a GPS unit, you can use it to get an even wider version of this view.
2

2
For a more detailed view, ~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37mlmap~1b[22m~1b[36m~1b[22m will show you locations surrounding your current position, along with lines showing obvious exits, and an annotated legend explaining what each location is.
2

2
In all maps, the () in the middle represents your location.
