Repairing things is a valuable skill used to fix up shit when it breaks. And shit will break. Repairing things depends on your repair skill, which depends on your brains. To repair something, simply type ~1b[1m~1b[37mrepair <item>~1b[22m~1b[36m.
2

2
Repairing is separated into three general categories: Broken ~1b[1mweapons,~1b[22m worn-down ~1b[1marmor,~1b[22m and anything else.
2

2
For ~1b[1mweapons,~1b[22m there's a whole section dedicated to it; see ~1b[1mhelp~1b[22m ~1b[1mweapon-repair.~1b[22m
2

2
~1b[1mArmor~1b[22m is an interesting thing to repair. ~1b[1mArmor~1b[22m has ~1b[1mHP,~1b[22m and the lower the ~1b[1mHP~1b[22m value, the less protection it offers. When the armor's ~1b[1mHP~1b[22m gets to 0, the ~1b[1marmor~1b[22m will break, leaving you armorless. Repairing your ~1b[1marmor~1b[22m will restore it to max ~1b[1mhealth,~1b[22m but its max ~1b[1mhealth~1b[22m will be lowered by 1, so eventually you will have to replace that ~1b[1marmor~1b[22m (though not for a long while.) Be careful when repairing ~1b[1marmor,~1b[22m too: If you *really* suck at repairing ~1b[1marmor,~1b[22m you'll destroy the ~1b[1marmor~1b[22m a bit more, taking a way a hit point. To see how much ~1b[1mHP~1b[22m the ~1b[1marmor~1b[22m has, ~1b[1mwear~1b[22m it and type ~1b[1m~1b[37mworn~1b[22m~1b[36m.
2

2
Repairing anything else is quite easy, since you don't have to worry too much about it breaking all the way from your failed repairs. Anything in a very smashed state is pretty unusable, so if someone smashes in your door, you won't be able to close it till you repair it a bit. Definitely keep that repair skill up, unless you're willing to pay for a repair every ~1b[1mtime.~1b[22m
2

2
