To rent an apartment, go to the lobby of any apartment building or hotel. ~1b[1m~1b[37mexam here~1b[22m~1b[36m to see what you can do in the lobby. See the ~1b[1m~1b[37mrent~1b[22m~1b[36m command? If you type that, you'll be assigned an apartment!
2

2
When you first rent an apartment, you'll be charged an upfront fee, followed by rent every ingame month, automatically deducted from your credchip. If you don't have enough for rent, you're evicted and your stuff is sent to Sargo's Discount Warehouse. Upfront charges and rent depend on the location: generally, the higher the charges, the better ~1b[1msecurity~1b[22m the place offers. In most apartment lobbies there's a sign that shows the monthly rent, the up-front cost, and whether there are vacancies.
2

2
If you can't afford an apartment, try the Crash Landing cube hotel. You can log off there and you'll be put in a sleeping cube, safe and sound with your ~1b[1mgear.~1b[22m
