The ~1b[1m~1b[37mgrab <creature>~1b[22m~1b[36m command lets you try to throw your arms around someone (or something) and ~1b[1mrestrain~1b[22m it. While you're restraining someone, you'll still be able to do things like ~1b[1mattack,~1b[22m but they'll be helpless! This means you can do things to them you wouldn't normally be allowed to do, like ~1b[1mfuck~1b[22m them. You can also use the otherwise ineffective ~1b[1m~1b[37mshove <creature> to <direction>~1b[22m~1b[36m command while you are restraining someone, allowing you to push someone through an unobstructed exit, as long as the exit isn't above your current location.
2

2
Your success at grabbing is based on your brawn and reflexes, whereas your target defends with its ~1b[1mdodge.~1b[22m Once you've grabbed them, it's your brawn versus their brawn and reflexes.
2

2
If you've been grabbed, there isn't much you can do about it but wait for your strength and reflexes to overcome your opponent and break you free. You can ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m yourself harder to grab by getting covered in oil (or some other slippery fluid), or with certain ~1b[1mmutations.~1b[22m
