The ~1b[1m~1b[37msearch~1b[22m~1b[36m command lets you search your current location for hidden or salvageable ~1b[1mitems.~1b[22m It uses ~1b[1mscavenge~1b[22m skill; the higher your ~1b[1mscavenge~1b[22m total, the more likely you are to find good loot.
2

2
Different ~1b[1mitems~1b[22m are found in different places; explore thoroughly and search in different types of locations repeatedly to see what you can turn up. With enough searching in one location, you will eventually exhaust it, and have to move on to a new spot for a while.
2

2
Some locations may have special hidden clues, ~1b[1mitems,~1b[22m or doors -- you'll often get a hint when entering such a room. Keep searching in that spot until you've found the secret. If you just can't find it, you might need to train up your ~1b[1mscavenge~1b[22m skill and come back.
2

2
Scavenging is a great way to ~1b[1mmake~1b[22m cash when you're just starting out, and for ~1b[1mcraft~1b[22m and ~1b[1mscience~1b[22m it's absolutely essential throughout your career. Most ingredients and components in the game are found via scavenging.
