~1b[1m~1b[1m~1b[37m@password~1b[22m <old-password> <new-password>~1b[22m~1b[36m
2

2
Changes your player's password (as typed in the connect command when you log in to the MOO) to <new-password>. For ~1b[1msecurity~1b[22m reasons, you are required to type your current (soon to be old) password as the first argument.
2

2
Your password is stored in an encrypted form in the MOO database; in principle, not even the ~1b[1mwizards~1b[22m can ~1b[1mtell~1b[22m what it is, though they can change it, of course. It is recommended that your password not be your name or a common word; MOO ~1b[1mpasswords~1b[22m have been stolen or cracked in the past and characters have been made unhappy by such theft. Your password is your security; choose a safe one.
2

2
If your character does get stolen, a wizard can change it for you and ~1b[1mtell~1b[22m you the new password in secret. You may have to provide your email address for verification.
