There are several ways to check the status of your character.  The most basic is simply to 'look me' for a quick visual check of your appearance; this can tell you about what you're wearing, your general health, and so on.  Another basic command is 'i' for 'inventory', to see what you're carrying around and how much it all weighs.  Other commands exist to give you more direct information.
2

2
'su' is the most basic -- just a one-line display of your health, XP, money, and any status effects on you.
2

2
'st' (or 'status') is a little more detailled -- you'll see your health, money, thirst, hunger, stress, longer descriptions of your status effects, your wanted level, and other miscellaneous info.
2

2
'sc' (or 'score') lists all your stats and skills, mutations, implants, XP, and other information about your progress.  See help skills for more information about this display.
2
  'ss' shows only the mutation/implant/XP info from 'sc'.
2
  'sk' shows only the skill list from 'sc'.
2

2
'sx' lists all your sexual fetishes.  You perv.
2

2
'gear' shows your current damage resistance from armor, and stats about the weapons you're currently carrying and how they'll generally perform for you.
2

2
'worn' shows all your currently worn armor and its condition and thickness.
2

2
'fac' (or 'factions') shows your faction standings (if any) and wanted levels.
2

2
'tac' (or 'tactical') shows the health and status of all combatants in your location.  This is essential for keeping up with the progress of a big fight.
2

2
See also: help skills, help stats, help gear, help health
