Help!  You're confused and disoriented and a little overwhelmed.  How do you find out what the fuck's going on?
2

2
For starters, there's this help system which you've just discovered.  'help' by itself will show you a list of topics; you can then 'help <topic>' to read about one of those.  'help <skill>' or 'help <mutation>' will tell you about a particular skill or mutation.
2

2
You can also get help from your fellow players using chatnet -- just type 'chat Hey where is Slim Stabby found?' and your question will be broadcast to everyone on chatnet.  If you need more personalized real-time assistance, 'page help <message>' will send a message directly to the game's administrators.  If someone's awake to answer your question, you'll probably get some kind of useful response.
2

2
As you're out exploring, you can get information about the things in your environment on your own.  You can learn a lot just by looking at things!  Try 'look <object>', 'look <creature>', or even 'look <direction>' to look more closely at someone or something.  You can also find out what obvious commands are available on a given item or location with 'exam <item>' or 'exam here'.  Some items even have a help file attached; try 'help <item>'.
2

2
Don't forget to keep tabs on your own condition -- see help status for more info.
