2
Items items everywhere.  Look at all this shit!  Is any of it even useful?
2

2
Almost everything you find is good for something.  But there's so much of it, you need priorities -- you can't carry everything.  Here are a few broad classes of items you'll find on your travels:
2

2
- Weapons.  Guns, swords, clubs, spears, etc.  You probably want at least one at all times.
2

2
- Clothing.  Shirts, pants, armor, helmets, gloves.  Unless you're counting on your mutation abilities or dodge to save you, you probably want some armor.  Check the Protect Ya Neck shop.
2

2
- Containers.  Packs, satchels, bags.  Putting your junk in a container helps you carry more of it.  Essential!
2

2
- Cocoons.  Carry a cocoon at all times (NOT in a container!) and you can rest a little easier about the fate of your gear should you take the big dirt nap.
2

2
- Artifacts.  Parts, materials, pogs, tamagotchis, spools of wire, etc.  Most of these are useful for crafting various recipes and schematics.  Aside from that, almost all can be sold to Avram at Salvage Unlimited (or other similar shops) for quick and easy cash.
2

2
- Food and water.  Meals, meat, canteens, soda.  You probably want some of these at all times.
2

2
- Medical items.  Trauma kits, nanites, medicine hypos, suture kits, defibrillators, insta-casts.  If you've got any medic skill at all, keep some of these around for when luck doesn't go your way.
2

2
- Drugs.  Speed, cocaine, weed, supajunk, heroin, booze, etc.  Some give you useful bonuses; some help you destress.
2

2
- Tools.  Climbing ropes, fishing poles, portable stoves -- many items exist to help you in specific situations or tasks.  Check Eschaton Outfitters or Hell Up In Hardware for a wide variety.  Experiment to find what helps you the most.
