A disturbing array of chat networks are available to you from your trusty wristpad. The most obvious (and the one you start the game subscribed to) is chatnet. You can turn it on and off with 'chatnet on' or 'chatnet off'.  When it's on, chat by typing something like 'chat Hi guys!'. 'chatnet who' will show you who else is awake and listening to the net, and 'chatnet history' will show you a fair bit of past conversation on the net.
2

2
Other networks work basically the same way -- type the network's name plus 'on' or 'off' to toggle them, the name plus 'who' or 'history' to see who is online or the history of that net, and the first part of the name (without net) to talk.  Networks available to you include:
2

2
- chatnet - General chatter, asking questions about the game or the world, looking for advice or assistance.
2
- tradenet - Buying and selling items and services.
2
- zotnet - Talking to the admins about game bugs and ideas. WARNING: Since you will be dealing with the admins on this net, choose your words carefully. Idiots and whiners who come on this net are often kicked out for three months at a time.
2
- djnet - This channel is for HellMOO's own admin-run radio station at http://tspigot.net:8000 .  We love it when players request music!  To see what's playing, type 'djnet info', and to see the schedule, type 'djnet schedule'.
2
 - playnet - A net for talking about games that aren't HellMOO. Use 'pl <text>' or 'pla <text>' to talk on this net.
2
- mailnet - Mailnet tracks activity on several of the mailing lists (see 'help mail' and 'help mail2' for more info on the mail system). Use this net to watch them for new posts, up/downvotes, status changes, and comments on existing posts. You cannot chat on mailnet.
2
 - jailnet - Unlike most nets, you can use jailnet while in Panopticon Prison (this is, in fact, the only place you can use it). It's for you to chat with other criminals in there and for the admins to laugh at your misfortune.
2
 - dongnet - Dongnet is a net run by Dionysus and his chatbot Donginger. Donginger can do various dumb things (listed at http://hellmoo.org/~dionysus/donginger.html) for you.
2
 - trollnet - The worst net.
2

2
If you're hired into a corp, you'll also have a corporate net on which to chat.  Turn corpnet on/off with 'corpnet on|off', and chat with simply 'c'.
