Fuck it -- let's go get a drink!  Eventually as you wander the wastes, you'll start feeling thirsty.  'st' will tell you exactly how thirsty you are.  Guess what you can do about it?
2

2
Sources of water (or something approximating water) are all over the place.  Showers and sinks, rivers, lakes, the ocean, stagnant underground pools of waste -- you can drink from all of them.  If that doesn't appeal to you, try some Bebop Cola -- soda machines are all over FC.
2

2
'Examine' your surroundings carefully.  When you see something that common sense says you could drink from, 'exam' it to see if your initial feeling was a bit silly, and to tell whether it has liquid in it. When you drink from a finite fluid source such as a canteen, glass of water, or rusty barrel, the amount of fluid in it will go down.  'Look' at the object to determine how much liquid is left in it.
2

2
Water sources generally have three commands:
2
- 'drink', which fills your belly full of the wet stuff.
2
- 'smell', which tells you whether your potential drinking target seems safe.
2
- 'wash', which removes the blood/jizz/oil from your body.  Note that this command will deplete a finite water source.
2

2
Being a thirsty stranger in strange lands incurs large stat penalties, so carry your own water source everywhere. Just be sure you filled it from something that won't kill you!
2

2
See also: help hunger, help urination
