So, you've just been killed, and the evil other players are camping your gear. You've got no weapons, no armor, and no hope. Well, then turn to the exciting world of explosives! 
2

2
Currently in the world there are two main types of explosives: Single-area explosives will only affect things in the room the bomb goes off in. These include pipe bombs, molotov cocktails, and all grenade types. There are also multi-room explosives which affect a certain number or radius of rooms from the detonation point. Examples of those are metal suitcases and clusternuke pellets. Some explosives(the clusternuke pellet and dirty bomb) cause radiation to the area they go off in, so be prepared to use a rad detox on yourself if you enter this area. 
2

2
Some explosives do not do BANG! damage, but rather have an effect on the people in the room. For example, a THC grenade will get you high, a stun grenade will stun you, etc. Feel like taking someone with you when you want to explode? Then wear a suicide belt and show Allah that you want your virgins and now! 
2

2
Now, where can you find these explosives? There are stores in both Botany Bay and New Clearwater that sell most explosives, but almost all of them can be crafted. Note: To use explosives effectively you will need to be adequately suited in the bombs skill.  You'll want to get this skill up unless you like playing explosive Russian Roulette.
