Dodge is one of the many skills in your 'sc' sheet.  It has an important role in combat -- it lets you avoid attacks!  The higher your dodge, the more likely you'll dodge completely away from an attack.  Even if this doesn't happen, your dodge makes your enemy less likely to land a blow effectively.
2

2
Your dodge, like any skill, can be affected by many factors.  Wearing cumbersome armor will lower your dodge.  Certain medical problems like a broken leg or arm won't be helping much either.  Carrying too much weight slows you down too much to dodge well.  Watch your 'sc' display closely, and you may discover other factors.
2

2
Dodge skill is also used outside of combat, most notably for avoiding explosion damage and escaping a grab attempt.
2

2
Aside from this passive dodging, you can also use the 'dodge' command in combat to devote yourself to dodging for a short time.  If timed right, this can be a lifesaver against an incoming powerattack or other major damage.
2

2
See also: help parry, help skills, help combatoptions
