Parrying is an automatic defense in melee vs. melee combat, in which the defender knocks away the opponent's strike with his own weapon skill.  All weapons have a parry class of 0, 1, or 2; a weapon can only parry weapons of an equal or lower class (check parry class in the 'gear' display).  A piston hammer (parry class 2) can parry a butcher knife (parry class 1), but not vice versa.
2

2
The higher your weapon skill, the more likely you'll parry.  Parrying will sometimes cost you whatever action you were about to perform -- you'll get a message about this if it happens.  With higher weapon skill these interrupt parries will happen less often, as you'll be swatting away blows gracefully without stopping your own actions.
361
5
4
