You might have noticed that sometimes you get cold, or hot.  This should be pretty intuitive; some places are hot and some are cold.  It generally gets colder at night, and in the winter.  Some areas of the world are hotter or colder than others.  And being near certain things (like campfires) might make you heat up.
2

2
This isn't just an idle curiosity; being cold or hot will affect your skills and stats, and mostly not for the better.  Extreme cold can slowly freeze you to death, and burning heat will slowly bake you.
2

2
There are several simple ways to deal with temperature extremes:
2

2
- Be aware!  The 'time' command doesn't just show the time, but also the air temperature (and the temperature you're actually feeling).
2
- Be smart!  If you need to travel through the desert, consider going at night.  Planning an expedition to summit Fisty?  Wait until early afternoon.
2
- Dress for success!  Parkas and snowpants, or burqas and dishdashas, most clothing has some effect.
2
- Mutate!  Many mutants can resist extreme heat or cold.
