As we know from movies, if you have a sword, you either hit someone with it or you don't, there's no real in-between.  But with guns, half the fun is in pointing them at people and acting like a bigshot!
2

2
If you've got a gun, just 'aim <gun> at <person>'.  Did you know that's a crime?  Ha ha!  Several hilarious things might happen now:
2

2
- If your victim's an NPC, they'll probably just start attacking you.
2
- If your victim has good dodge, they'll roll out of your aim and come up fighting.
2
- If your victim has a gun (and high pistol skill), they might pull a gun back at you.
2
- Most likely your victim will be frozen in terror.
2

2
Now you've got the drop on him!  If he performs any action at all, you'll immediately fire and do damage (probably).  If not, you'll be gaining stress every few seconds until you type 'stop', or run away or do something else.  To fire, just 'kill <person>'.
2

2
You can also aim your gun at an exit.  This only works on a door, or any exit indoors.  If anyone comes through from the other side, you'll fire on them immediately.
