2
You might have seen a message something like this at some point:
2

2
'You have received new mail (2) from Gilmore.'
2

2
To read your mail, type '@nn' for your next unread message.  If you'd like to read over old mail, try '@mail', then '@peek <number>'.
2

2
To send a message, simply '@qsend playername Hey man whats up?  You owe me $5000 asshole!'.  To send a message of multiple lines, '@send playername', hit return, then type your message.  When you're done, type '.' on a line by itself. @qsend (short for @quicksend) also allows you to send a message of multiple lines if used the same way.
2

2
There are many mailing lists you can subscribe to as well.  Read 'help lists' for a list of the lists that you would ever actually use.  To subscribe to any list, just '@subscribe *listname'.  If you're in a corp, your corp has its own mailing list only readable by employees, called *c-SYMBOL (where SYMBOL is your corp's symbol).
2

2
Now whenever you '@nn', if you don't have any new personal mail, you'll read the next message on one of your lists.  If you don't feel like reading through all of a list, simply '@skip *listname'.  If you're tired of a list, '@unsubscribe *listname'.  '@mail on *list' and '@peek <number> on *list' will also work as you'd expect, and you can post to a list with '@send *listname Does anyone here like coldplay?'.
2

2
Popular lists include:
2

2
- '*rumors' - Admins post rumors here about events in the world.
2
- '*changelog-public' - *clp for short.  Admins post gamesystem changes here.
2
- '*comedy' - Player-writable.  Funny occurences in hell.
2
- '*bugs' - Players send bugs here; admins hopefully fix em.
2
- '*ideas' - Players send ideas here; admins hopefully make em.
2
- '*shenanigans' - Players send ridiculous things they did with the game system here.
2

2
Most of these lists also let you vote for posts you like/hate -- '@yes 123 on *ideas', or '@no 4456 on *comedy'.
2

2
For advanced mail topics, like message sequences, voting, and commenting, read 'help mail2'.
2
For any more mail commands, like removing or forwarding mail, see 'help mail-index'.
2
For a more detailed list of the mailing lists, read 'help lists'.
2

2
'REMEMBER TO TURN ON MAILNET!' Mailnet is for tracking new posts, comments, and votes across all (or at least most) of the mailing lists. Just type 'mailnet on' and it will begin telling you everything. Unlike other nets, you cannot chat on mailnet.
