2
If you just want to quit for the evening and come back later, you'll need to get somewhere safe first.  An apartment is ideal, but if you're a poor newbie, you can always go to the Crash Landing cube hotel (it's marked CL on the map).  Just walk in and type '@quit' to disconnect.
2

2
Using @quit/@forcequit/@ragequit/@joyquit will successfully log you off. Sometimes closing your client or refreshing your Charon page does not log you off, so if you log onto your alt, you will share a connection. To make the admins' lives more easier, stop us wasting time on telling you to log off properly and let us get back to nerfing.
2

2
If you were trying to quit your corp, try 'corp resign'.
2

2
If you're just utterly disgusted with the game and you never want to come back, well...have you tried Dwarf Fortress?
2

2
You'll be back, though. They always come back.
