No, no fish.
2

2
Mining is very simple. Grab a pickaxe from your local supplies shop, find the nearest dark cave, and start breaking away. Some cave tunnels aren't so stable however, and are prone to collapse. Be wary of such areas.
2
Within those dangerous areas are most likely some support beams, which can be used to buffer the caves from collapsing as quickly; Chances are they will need to be repaired. This can be done using material that the beam is made out of (scrap wood for wooden supports, lead bars for lead beams, etc). They wont last forever though, so be prepared to have to repair it again.
2

2
Mining is a continuous action which will unearth various minerals and/or ores in the room you are mining in. The extent of how long you can mine without stopping is determined by your Endurance. The higher it is, the longer you can go without stopping.
2
While mining, you can gain muscle strain. Try using creatine if you find yourself pulling a few too many muscles.
2

2
That's all there is to it. Grab a miner's helmet and go to town on those rocks (who happen to be hoarding all of the good gems)!
