MCP, or MUD Client Protocol, lets the MOO send your client information "out of band", or outside of the normal text stream. MCP information gets sent to your client and enables special features, like your current health, hunger, illnesses, etc in your status bar.
2

2
MCP support is very experimental. Currently we know of the following clients that support MCP:
2

2
 * VMoo: http://www.vmoo.com/
2

2
 * TinyFugue: http://tinyfugue.sourceforge.net/
2
  (You'll need the mcp21 packages at:
2
   http://moosaico.com/clients/mcp21-tf-packages.tar.gz )
2

2
 * zMUD: http://www.zuggsoft.com/zmud/
2

2
Let us know (with '@qsend Seraph blah blah blah' or something) if you have any comments or you get it working on any other clients. We will also probably mess with some other forms of this -- unfortunately, the most popular client among Hellmooers, SimpleMU, doesn't seem to support anything like this.
