A rupture is a tear in the fabric of the world. It means something has gone horribly, horribly wrong.
2

2
A rupture occurs when, for some reason, some bit of code is unable to run the way it was written. If you cause a rupture directly you will see it happen, but many times you may not.
2

2
Reporting a rupture is not necessary. Do not file a bug report or ask about it on zotnet. The admins are informed when a rupture occurs and given all relevant info.
2

2
That being said, if admin approaches you directly for more information regarding a rupture, do cooperate. It can sometimes be unclear as to what exactly caused the issue at hand and we may need help from you to find and fix the problem.
2

2
Admins may refer from time to time to 'tracebacks'. A traceback is fancy-talk for a rupture.
