In general, you can't be attacked by another player -- with the following exceptions.
2

2
  - If a player challenges you (see help challenge), you can attack them at any time to answer the challenge.
2
  - If a player has deleted their clone and gone hardcore (see help hardcore), they can attack you at any time!  The first time they do this, they become an outlaw (see help outlaw).
2
  - No newbie-level player can attack or be attacked at all.
2
  - If a player hacks your corp's gangland cams, they auto-challenge your entire corp, and you can attack them in revenge at any time.
2
  - Any players in an open PvP area can attack each other at any time.  If you enter such an area, you'll be notified of the danger.
2
  - If you are wearing a fursuit, anyone can attack you. Don't wear a fursuit.
2

2
So in general, if you don't start any shit, you're safe except from outlaws.  Outlaws are marked on the 'who' list with a red +, and can be identified with 'appraise'.
2

2
Note that, although you can probably find actions like 'aim' or 'spray', or the use of explosives or thrown objects, which will let you hurt or kill people you aren't technically allowed to attack, that this counts as being a huge dick.  If you do this, you'll be erased from the game.
