2
So, what do you look like? What do you want other players to see when they look at you? To describe yourself, type '@describe me as <description>' or '@desc me as <description>'.
2

2
Whatever you type is what people will see when they use the 'look' command on you.
2

2
Example:
2
Ammut types:
2
  '@describe me as \"More like a ham than a man, really.\"'
2
People who type 'look Ammut' now see:
2
  More like a ham than a man, really.
2

2
You are encouraged to be creative. You can also describe your nude body parts with '@nude <part> is <description>', which will show whenever that part of your body is uncovered.
2

2
Example: '@nude back is \"%P back is covered in horrible burn scars.\"' Here \"%P\" is replaced with \"His\", \"Her\", or \"Its\" depending on your gender. See 'help pronouns' for help on using that (it does not work with '@describe', only in the nude body part descriptions).
2

2
Note: Do not use descriptions (@nude or otherwise) to pretend you have things you don't (for example, using the worn descriptions for various pieces of armor in-game, etc.). Doing this will at least get your description privileges removed, or possibly banned.
