19
2
This object can be used to create a VR element that allows players to sit down or recline.  It could be used for standard furniture, like a couch or a chair, or used more generally to as the base for anything that allows someone to sit or lie on it (tables, pillows, whatever).
2
Properties:
2
  .seats -- the number of people who can sit on this thing (reclining takes up two seats)
2
Messages:
2
  There are a slew of them for various situations, see @messages $furniture
2
Verbs:
2
  sit on this -- queues a sit action for player with this as the target
2
  recline on this -- queues a recline action for player with this as the target
2
  stand from this -- queues a stand action for the player with this as the target
2

2
Tutorial:
2
@create $furniture named "loveseat"
2
#loveseat.seats = 2;
2
@describe loveseat as "A tattered plaid loveseat."
2
@look_place_msg loveseat is "You see a tattered %t here."
2
drop loveseat
2
sit on loveseat
2
recline on loveseat
2
stand form loveseat
