12
2
This is a type of workbench -- a crafting station for making new things out of old things.  Crafting mostly uses craft skill (though other skills may be required -- consult your recipe!) and can not only get you some items unobtainable anywhere else, but also earns you XP.
2

2
How to use:
2

2
(1) Find a recipe (or turn a recipe book to a recipe page).
2
(2) Gather up all the ingredients called for in the recipe.
2
(3) Put the ingredients AND the recipe (or recipe book) into the workbench.
2
(4) 'make workbench'.
2

2
If all goes well (and you have sufficient skill) you'll make a new item, using up the ingredients.  The new item will be found in the workbench.  If all doesn't go well, you not only won't make an item, you might lose one or more of the ingredients.
2

2
For mass-crafting, you can load up the workbench with a lot of each ingredient, then repeat the 'make' command several times.  You can also put several recipes on the workbench, and differentiate between them with 'make <recipe> on workbench'.
