%DN turns %dt to %state.
361
5
2
%DT is set to %state.
361
5
4
38
2
The $switch is simply an immobile object which players can set to one of a selection of states (for instance, "on" and "off").  This does nothing on its own; however, you can read the switch's state from some other object and make changes elsewhere based on it, or have the switch notify other objects when its state changes.
2

2
Properties:
2

2
states = LIST
2
  A list of strings, naming all the states to which the switch can be set.
2

2
reset_state = STR
2
  One of the above states -- the state to which the switch is set on an area reset.
2

2
reveal_states = INT (boolean)
2
  If true, show the player all possible states if she tries to set the switch to an invalid state.
2

2
listeners = LIST
2
  A list of objects with a :hear_switch(this, state) intended to hear state changes from this switch.
2

2
state = STR (read-only)
2
  You can check this property to see what state the switch is in.
2

2

2
Commands:
2

2
switch/turn/set <this> to <any>
2
turn <this> <any>
2
  The one and only player command for switches -- turn the switch to a different state.
2

2

2
Verbs:
2

2
:switch_to(STR state)
2
  Called when the player switches the switch to a new state.  Also notifies any .listeners of the state change by calling listener:hear_switch(this, state).
2

2
:on_reset()
2
  Resets the switch to its .reset_state.
2

2
:tell_setting()
2
  When the player looks at the switch, this describes its state to her.
2

